# Goal: move a plate / lid / generic resource to another location.
# `transport` ∈ {"iswap", "core", "auto"}. "core" requires a CoRe gripper held;
# "iswap" requires the iSWAP module; "auto" lets the node pick based on
# availability (iSWAP first, CoRe as fallback).
# `pickup_direction` / `drop_direction` ∈ {"front", "back", "left", "right"}.
#
# Hotel mode is auto-detected: if ``to`` names a resource that is also
# a registered handoff (see ``~/define_handoff``), the server routes
# through pylabrobot's ``use_unsafe_hotel=True`` path (STAR firmware
# ``PO``/``PI``) and pulls ``hotel_depth`` + ``hotel_clearance_height``
# from the registered record. For explicit overrides (tuning, or
# hotel-via-non-handoff-name corner cases) the bool + floats below are
# honoured when non-default.
string resource
string to
string transport
string pickup_direction
string drop_direction
geometry_msgs/Vector3 pickup_offset
geometry_msgs/Vector3 destination_offset
bool use_unsafe_hotel                   # force on (even if ``to`` isn't a handoff)
float32 hotel_depth                     # 0 = registered value, or pylabrobot default
float32 hotel_clearance_height          # 0 = registered value, or pylabrobot default
float32 pickup_distance_from_top        # 0 = resource's preferred pickup
---
bool success
string message
string[] warnings
---
float32 progress
string stage
